activities.name: City Palace
activities.description: Visit the City Palace, a beautiful blend of Mughal and Rajasthani architecture. Explore the museums and courtyards.
activities.notes: Due to the extreme heat, stay hydrated and wear light clothing. The City Palace offers shaded areas.

activities.name: Jantar Mantar
activities.description: Explore the astronomical observatory, a UNESCO World Heritage Site.
activities.notes: Visit early in the morning or late in the afternoon to avoid the peak heat.

activities.name: Hawa Mahal
activities.description: See the iconic Palace of Winds. Take photos from the outside or go inside to experience the architecture.
activities.notes: Best viewed from outside or early morning when the temperature is relatively lower.

food.name: Laxmi Misthan Bhandar (LMB)
food.description: Enjoy traditional Rajasthani cuisine in a comfortable, air-conditioned environment.
food.notes: Try the Dal Baati Churma and Ghevar.

food.name: Rawat Misthan Bhandar
food.notes: Try their famous pyaz ki kachori

activities.name: Amber Fort
activities.description: Visit Amber Fort, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Explore the palaces, temples, and gardens.
activities.notes: Opt for an early morning visit to avoid the heat. Consider taking an air-conditioned taxi or car. Elephant ride is optional. The fort has many shaded areas and AC halls.

activities.name: Jal Mahal
activities.description: Take photos of the Water Palace from the lakeside. No entry to the palace.
activities.notes: Quick stop. Best visited in the evening when the temperature is cooler.

activities.name: Albert Hall Museum
activities.description: Visit the oldest museum of the state of Rajasthan

food.name: Suvarna Mahal at Rambagh Palace
food.description: Enjoy a luxurious dining experience with authentic Indian cuisine.
food.notes: Prior booking is recommended. It's a pricier option but offers a royal experience.

important_notes: Travel during May can be very hot in Jaipur. It is advised to stay hydrated, wear light clothing, and plan activities during the cooler parts of the day (early morning or late afternoon/evening). Always check the weather forecast closer to your travel dates for the most accurate information.
